-- Heritage Oil Faces Shareholder Revolt on Pay, Telegraph Says
-- B y   A b i g a i l   M o s e s
-- 2012-06-17T13:44:05Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-17/heritage-oil-faces-shareholder-revolt-over-pay-telegraph-says.html
Heritage Oil Plc faces shareholder
opposition over executive pay at its June 21 annual meeting
after investor groups criticized its policies and urged them to
be voted down, the  Sunday Telegraph  reported.  The  Association of British Insurers  and Pensions Investment
Research Consultants are among critics of the company’s two-year
notice period for directors, the newspaper said.  Nick Lambert, spokesman for Heritage, didn’t return a
message left outside of office hours.  To contact the reporter on this story:
